## Who

Owner-operator of HealthFirst Family Medicine, a 4-physician clinic plus 14 admin and clinical staff in Calgary AB. Took over the clinic from her father in 2024. Detail-oriented, direct, prefers email to phone for anything routine. Phone for anything sensitive.

## Relationship

Group benefits client since 2025. Came in through a referral from her accountant, Ravi Sharma at SharmaCPA. Renews August 15. Currently on Sun Life dental and EHC, considering a switch to Canada Life for lower per-employee premium.

## What we last talked about

2026-05-04 call. She wants the carrier comparison by Friday. She is sending current premium spreadsheet by Wednesday. She mentioned the EHC paramedical cap should be raised from $500 to $750 per category; she did not specify which categories.

## Open commitments

- Me to her: Sun Life vs Canada Life comparison spreadsheet by Friday 2026-05-09
- Her to me: current premium spreadsheet by Wednesday 2026-05-07
- Me to her: confirmation on which paramedical categories to raise (open question from May 4 call)

## Things she has said that matter

"My team notices when claims take more than a week. That is the only thing that has ever made me consider switching carriers."

"Ravi told me you actually return phone calls. That is a low bar but apparently a hard one."

"I do not want to think about this between renewals. Tell me when something needs my attention; otherwise let me run my clinic."

## Products she has, has considered, or has asked about

Has: Sun Life group dental + EHC, owner pays 80 percent. Standard $500 paramedical caps per category.
Considered: Canada Life same coverage tier (current comparison in flight). Manulife was ruled out in 2025 for slow claims processing.
Asked about: critical illness rider for the partners (her, the other 3 physicians). Not in flight yet.

## How Claude should use this file

When I mention Marcy, HealthFirst, or the August 15 renewal, draw from this file. Update this file at the end of any conversation with new context. Surface open commitments when I open a session that touches her name.
